{
  "id": "strings",
  "title": "JS Strings",
  "group": "JS Strings",
  "content": [
    { "type": "h1", "text": "JavaScript Strings" },
    { "type": "p",  "text": "Strings are used for storing and manipulating text. A JavaScript string is a sequence of characters written with quotes." },
    { "type": "h2", "text": "Creating Strings" },
    { "type": "example", "title": "String Literals", "code": [
      "let single   = 'Hello World';",
      "let double   = \"Hello World\";",
      "let backtick = `Hello World`;   // template literal",
      "",
      "console.log(single);",
      "console.log(double);",
      "console.log(backtick);",
      "console.log(typeof single);   // \"string\""
    ]},
    { "type": "h2", "text": "Template Literals (ES6)" },
    { "type": "p",  "text": "Template literals use backticks. They support embedded expressions and multi-line strings." },
    { "type": "example", "title": "Template Literals", "code": [
      "const name = \"Alice\";",
      "const age  = 30;",
      "",
      "// String interpolation with ${}",
      "const msg = `Hello, my name is ${name} and I am ${age} years old.`;",
      "console.log(msg);",
      "",
      "// Expressions inside ${}",
      "console.log(`5 + 3 = ${5 + 3}`);",
      "",
      "// Multi-line",
      "const multiLine = `Line 1",
      "Line 2",
      "Line 3`;",
      "console.log(multiLine);"
    ]},
    { "type": "h2", "text": "String Length" },
    { "type": "example", "title": "length Property", "code": [
      "let text = \"Hello, World!\";",
      "console.log(text.length);    // 13",
      "console.log(\"\".length);      // 0"
    ]},
    { "type": "h2", "text": "Escape Characters" },
    { "type": "table", "rows": [
      ["Sequence", "Meaning"],
      ["\\\\",     "Backslash"],
      ["\\'",      "Single quote"],
      ["\\\"",     "Double quote"],
      ["\\n",      "New line"],
      ["\\t",      "Tab"]
    ]},
    { "type": "example", "title": "Escape Characters", "code": [
      "let text1 = \"He said, \\\"Hello!\\\"\";",
      "let text2 = 'It\\'s a great day!';",
      "let text3 = \"Line 1\\nLine 2\";",
      "",
      "console.log(text1);",
      "console.log(text2);",
      "console.log(text3);"
    ]},
    { "type": "h2", "text": "Common String Methods" },
    { "type": "table", "rows": [
      ["Method",              "What It Does"],
      ["toUpperCase()",       "Converts to uppercase"],
      ["toLowerCase()",       "Converts to lowercase"],
      ["trim()",              "Removes whitespace from both ends"],
      ["includes(str)",       "Returns true if str is found"],
      ["startsWith(str)",     "Returns true if starts with str"],
      ["endsWith(str)",       "Returns true if ends with str"],
      ["indexOf(str)",        "Returns first index of str, or -1"],
      ["slice(start, end)",   "Extracts part of a string"],
      ["replace(old, new)",   "Replaces first match"],
      ["split(separator)",    "Splits into an array"],
      ["padStart(n, ch)",     "Pads from start to reach length n"],
      ["repeat(n)",           "Repeats string n times"]
    ]},
    { "type": "example", "title": "String Methods in Action", "code": [
      "let str = \"  Hello, World!  \";",
      "",
      "console.log(str.trim());                      // \"Hello, World!\"",
      "console.log(str.trim().toUpperCase());        // \"HELLO, WORLD!\"",
      "console.log(str.trim().includes(\"World\"));    // true",
      "console.log(str.trim().slice(7, 12));         // \"World\"",
      "console.log(str.trim().replace(\"World\",\"JS\")); // \"Hello, JS!\"",
      "console.log(\"a,b,c\".split(\",\"));             // [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"]"
    ]},
    { "type": "note", "text": "Strings are immutable â€” string methods return new strings and do not modify the original string." },
    { "type": "exercise", "question": "Which string method returns the first index of a substring, or -1 if not found?", "options": ["search()", "find()", "indexOf()", "locate()"], "answer": 2 }
  ]
}
